reviews.name: Mandp Kaur
reviews.text: Really really bad experience first of all the weather was awful but wants to treat family in that restaurant with small kids… went there around 6:30 not one comes until 7to get an order then got starters around 08:00pm then no one literally no one comes to ask about food or anything then around 08:40 ask them if they going to serve us a main meal and they said they are just preparing and actually they forgot about us then the guy went to the kitchen to ask about our food and said he is just going to bring our food and afterwards he served 5-6 table meals and then we got our meal… They should have prioritise people with the kids really wants to leave the table in between as no one cares there… and we order Indian style but still we got sweet taste of chicken and butter paneer… Really worst experience so bad guys…Really disappointed
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Thank you for sharing your feedback, we’re really sorry to hear about your experience. That evening was extremely busy and the restaurant was fully packed, but even in those situations our standard is to deliver attentive and timely service. We’re proud to be a highly rated restaurant and we always aim to provide quality food and care for every guest, especially families with little ones.

Unfortunately, we were also short a staff member that night, and we acknowledge that our service fell short of the standard we expect from ourselves. Our team was still giving their best under pressure, but we understand how the delays and miscommunication would have been frustrating for you.

We truly apologise for the inconvenience caused  particularly with your kids waiting so long. This isn’t the experience we want anyone to have, and we’re reviewing our processes to ensure this doesn’t happen again on busy nights.

We’d love the chance to welcome you back and show you the level of service we’re known for.

Thank you 
Bishnu (owner)
